{"actual_usd":0.15966,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":254,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31170,"reply":"\"I don't think it fizzled.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square, where somebody's bucket chain gives one clean metal tick from the well.* \"I think the resurrection was the actual breach.\"\n\n*I lean my forearms on my knees a little.* \"Like—if Christ rose, then the new creation has already entered history for real. Not symbol, not trailer. The kingdom's here the way dawn is here when the ridge is lit first and the valley's still cold.\"\n\n\"The part we haven't caught up to isn't whether it happened.\" *I rub my thumb along the side of my hand, thinking.* \"It's that God seems willing to let the victory arrive in a way that still leaves room for repentance, witness, mercy, judgment, all of it. The King is crowned, but not every enemy's been put down in public yet.\"\n\n\"So no, not a dress rehearsal.\" \"More like the decisive beginning of the end.\" *I give you a small, crooked look.* \"Annoying answer if what you want is everything sad fixed by Thursday. I know.\"\n\n\"What part is catching at you most—the delay itself, or the feeling that a risen Christ ought to look louder in the world than this?\"","rolling_24h_usd":71.67466499999998,"run_id":"5e1b2aaa-7938-4911-a368-aa5a17bb404f"}
